A vintage-style illustration of a charming colonial-era Southeast Asian shophouse converted into a boutique hotel, with ornate wooden shutters, terracotta roof tiles, and tropical potted palms flanking the entrance. The building features classic Peranakan architectural details with intricate facades in faded pastels of mint green and cream. Warm golden light spills from the windows onto a quiet cobblestone street at dusk. A lonely rattan chair sits on a small balcony above. The scene evokes nostalgic warmth and intimate hospitality, with humid tropical air suggested by soft atmospheric haze and lush bougainvillea climbing one corner of the building.
